    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The view "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.vwFiscalYearsByBillingGroupContracts",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to provide a filtered list of fiscal years that are associated with billing group contracts. It selects fiscal year details from the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.FiscalYear",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table, but only includes those fiscal years that are referenced in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.BillingGroupContract",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table. This view is useful for scenarios where only active fiscal years tied to existing contracts are relevant, ensuring that the data presented is both current and applicable to ongoing business operations."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity of this view is low. It involves a straightforward selection of columns from a single table ("
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.FiscalYear",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ") with a simple filtering condition based on a subquery that retrieves distinct fiscal years from another table ("
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.BillingGroupContract",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "). There are no joins, aggregations, or complex calculations involved."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Data Model Analysis"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Billing.FiscalYear (USER_TABLE):",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " This table likely contains details about fiscal years, including their identifiers, descriptions, start and end dates, and an active status flag."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Billing.BillingGroupContract (USER_TABLE):",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " This table appears to store information about billing group contracts, including a reference to fiscal years. The presence of fiscal years in this table indicates active or relevant contracts for those periods."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The view effectively links these two tables by using a subquery to filter fiscal years that are actively referenced in contracts, ensuring that only pertinent fiscal year data is retrieved."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Context and Use Cases"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "This view is particularly useful for financial reporting and analysis within the context of billing operations. It can be used to:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Generate reports that focus on fiscal years with active billing contracts."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Support decision-making processes by providing a filtered view of fiscal periods relevant to current contracts."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Assist in auditing and compliance checks by ensuring that only fiscal years tied to contracts are considered."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Efficiency:",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " The view uses a subquery to filter fiscal years, which is efficient given the simplicity of the query. The use of "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "SELECT DISTINCT",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " ensures that only unique fiscal years are considered, minimizing redundancy."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Indexing:",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " Performance can be enhanced by ensuring that the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "FiscalYear",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " column in both tables is indexed, which would speed up the subquery execution and the filtering process."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Scalability:",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " As the data volume grows, the performance impact of the subquery should be monitored. If the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "BillingGroupContract",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " table becomes large, consider optimizing the subquery or using indexed views if necessary."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
